<item>
            <title>[LU-14050] ofd_access_log_reader off by one error in alr_sort_and_print_thread()</title>
                <link>https://jira.whamcloud.com/browse/LU-14050</link>
                <project id="10000" key="LU">Lustre</project>
                    <description>&lt;p&gt;There&apos;s a bug somewhere in &lt;tt&gt;alr_sort_and_print_thread()&lt;/tt&gt;. If only one file is being accessed then it won&apos;t be printed by &lt;tt&gt;ofd_access_log_reader&lt;/tt&gt;. I think there is an off by one error around &lt;tt&gt;cut/i&lt;/tt&gt; that causes us to print one fewer files than we should.&lt;/p&gt;</description>
                <environment></environment>
